The paper proposes an extension of the MAP-Elites algorithm for multi-task optimization, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm also involves machine learning techniques such as policy optimization (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the evaluation is conducted on a simulated robotic arm and a 6-legged robot, which are both systems related to control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
